---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About | n8than.dev" description="About me">
  <section class="container stagger">
    <h1 class="section-heading">About</h1>
    <blockquote class="epigraph">
      "He who has a why to live can bear almost any how."
      <cite>— Friedrich Nietzsche</cite>
    </blockquote>
    <p>
      I'm a developer based in San Diego building web applications that solve real problems for real
      people. I got here the long way around.
    </p>
    <p>
      I studied Computer Science from 2012 to 2020. During that time I struggled to build anything
      meaningful outside of coursework. Nothing I could make felt useful enough to actually pursue,
      and the motivation wasn't there. After graduating, the COVID pandemic was reshaping the world
      around me. I wanted to help. Not from behind a screen, but on the ground, serving the people
      who were putting themselves at risk every day.
    </p>
    <p>
      In 2021, at the height of the pandemic, I picked up a job at Scripps Mercy Hospital doing
      food service — cooking for hospital staff on the overnight shift, running the cafeteria by
      myself, and providing a place for people to escape into during their breaks. Running a shift
      alone was already demanding, and the more care I put into it, the more people showed up. The
      wait times and volume became a real problem I needed to solve.
    </p>
    <p>
      In 2025 I started building again. Instead of waiting for someone to hand me direction or
      tools, I just started solving a problem I could see. A food ordering system for the hospital
      staff I worked with. I spent the year iterating on it, rebuilding it from scratch multiple
      times to fully understand what I was doing and why. For the first time, I was making something
      for real users, solving a real problem.
    </p>
    <p>
      Three months after launching in January 2026, I had over 80 registered accounts. Staff
      could order from their floor and pick up when it was ready, no more waiting around in the
      cafeteria. It freed up time for patient care, quality breaks, and faster turnaround across the
      board. A small tool, but it measurably improved how the staff spent their night.
    </p>
    <p>
      AI tooling, Claude Code especially, accelerated that process. Not by writing code for me, but
      by making problems less intimidating. Obscure configuration issues, cryptic build errors,
      unfamiliar APIs. Things that used to mean hours of googling and guessing, I could now break
      down and understand in minutes. That shift let me spend my time on what actually matters:
      designing systems, engineering solutions, and building things.
    </p>
    <p>
      Now I'm building on that momentum. I want to engineer things for people and industries that
      matter — healthcare, infrastructure, the systems that hold communities together. Sympatheia,
      the idea that we're all connected and responsible for one another, is what drives the
      work. This portfolio and the projects in it are where that starts.
    </p>

    <blockquote class="epigraph">
      "Accept the things to which fate binds you, and love the people with whom fate brings you together, and do so with all your heart."
      <cite>— Marcus Aurelius</cite>
    </blockquote>

    <section class="links">
      <h2>Find me online</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <a href="https://github.com/Nyx000" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/sd-nhuse/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">LinkedIn</a>
        </li>
        <li><a href="mailto:hello@n8than.dev">Email</a></li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .container {
    max-width: 42rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: var(--space-lg) var(--space-md);
  }

  .section-heading {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-md);
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--color-border);
    display: inline-block;
  }

  .epigraph {
    border-left: 2px solid var(--color-accent);
    padding-left: var(--space-md);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    line-height: 1.75;
  }

  .epigraph cite {
    display: block;
    margin-top: var(--space-xs);
    font-style: normal;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
  }

  p {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.75;
  }

  .links {
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .links h2 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .links ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .links ul a {
    display: inline-block;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-muted);
    padding: 0.5em 1.25em;
    border-radius: 9999px;
    color: var(--color-text);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition:
      border-color 0.2s ease,
      color 0.2s ease;
  }

  .links ul a:hover {
    border-color: var(--color-accent);
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }
</style>
